hints:
All about hue: Color Cards can
help you with a faster streak!

Top of the game: Color Cards can be played
on top of any card of the same color

Reflect on this: Reflection Cards can
help you with a faster streak

Up to you: Reflection Cards can be played
anytime during a level

Trick Rita!: Use +5 or Wild when your deck’s  
low to reset Rita’s counter!

Pro Tip #98: Rita never removes Wild
or Windmill cards

Hop Off! You can see Hoppy the Frog getting
ready to jump one move before she does

Holy Squirrely: Tap Sunny the squirrel
on a level and he will move!

Howdy Farmer! Use your solitaire skills
to grow crops & Harvest rewards

Puppy Love: Your dog BFF
by your side. Search for him on the map!

Pro Tip #16: Use Undo to reverse
a bad move

Pro Tip #56: Use +5 Cards when you need just
a few extra Cards to complete a level

Pro Tip #19: Use Wild Cards
to complete more Streaks

Pro Tip #62: Achieve a Diamond Crate to get
maximum bonus picks at the end of your Crop

Pro Tip #80: Power-Ups increase your
chances of getting 3 Stars!

Golden Tip: Complete a pyramid at the
Golden Glade to increase your Harvest Bonus

Did You Know? The 1st Solitaire game
took place in 1788

Did You Know? Solitaire is also known as
"Patience" in many European countries

Did You Know? Avocados contain more fat
than any fruit or vegetable on earth!

Did You Know? Young sunflowers track
the sun’s movement

Green Tip #22: Use cold water for your laundry
to save up to 80% of the energy

Green Tip #23:  Switch to fluorescent
light bulbs to use 4 times less electricity

Green Tip #24:  You can recycle aluminum
an indefinite amount of times

Did You Know? Sam’s winged friend
was named by Solitaire players

Pro Tip #125: Use Power-Ups to increase
your chances of completing a level

A Player's Best Friend: Pet Sam the dog
and he will reward you with extra Credits

Pro Tip #432: Complete Streaks with Cards of
the same color
